Oct 6 2009 	Best Value Clean Rooms Great Staff.	I'm always very hesitant when a great price is offered. We were offered rooms at the Sahara @ $16 per night, but staying at the Excalibur was the best thing we ever did. The room was clean and offered a good view of the southern strip. We stayed on the 11th floor of Tower II. I think the only disappointment was the distance you had to walk to get to the casino from your car.This wasn't my first trip to Vegas, but it was for my two friends and we wanted to take full advantage of the weeks stay. The casino offered free games of chance ($5x2) and two free drinks ($5x2) every day we stayed at the hotel. This was to offset a $5.60 fee we were billed daily in addition to our $38 plus tax nightly room charges. The weeks stay was only $187.38, we received 2 free nights because we stayed the entire week. Considering that many of the other casinos were charging close to or over $100 per night, I think we made a great decision. The casino was packed daily, but got worse on Thursday, Friday and Saturday. There were plenty of comps being thrown around, but not for a group of guys, only for couples. So show/dinner/casino discounts were not offered to us in the casino. The TIX discount show booth is only 1/2 block from the Excalibur, so we didn't miss out getting discounts on shows we wanted to see. There is a 2 for 1 discount for those who stay at the Excalibur to the &quot;Tournament of Kings&quot; dinner show, so don't book this at checking if you are staying a few days. They don't offer the discount until you have stayed a few nights, but go down to the desk everyday! They will offer you comps you didn't receive at check in.The all you can eat &quot;All Day&quot; buffet is a great option for $25, but we didn't take them up on it since we were not willing to come back to the casino for lunch and dinner. They place a daily guide in your room of events that occur in the casino all week, plus there are other specials slipped under the door every morning. I will stay again, especially since we were only in our room to freshen up or sleep. By the end of the week we heard people being offered $189 per night @ the Luxor, but looking at the rooms, we were very happy with our decision to stay at the Excalibur for less than a nights stay at a neighboring casino.	
