Sep 22 2009 	Cheap Clean Fun	Some Girlfriends and I decided to take our first trip to Vegas and booked the Excalibur through southwestvacations.com after reading I don't know how many different reviews. This hotel ended up being perfect for what we were looking for. When we arrived it was only 12p in the afternoon and check-in wasnt for a few hours...but they allowed to check into our room anyway with no additional charge. We stayed in tower 1 like tower 2 a good distance away from the check-in desk but it really didnt matter to us. When we got up to our room everything was clean including the bathroom. They had a good amount of towels for everyone as well as extra toilet paper. Also what i really liked was since there were 5 of us we were given rooms right next to each other and we could access each others room because there was a door within the room. I am picky when it comes to the beds...but my bed was clean and soft...my only complaint was that the pillows weren't the best. Also just to set the record straight, there are no refridgerators or microwaves....so we ended up buying a styrofoam coolers to keep water, juice, and LIQ cool. Also, there is a tram that will take you from the excalibur into the Luxor and Mandalay bay hotels, which can be accessed within the hotel. If you prefer to walk, just go up to the second floor of the main tower, where the casino is and you can walk right through the hotels. The buffet in excalibur is the greatest, ended up getting the $30 bracelet to eat as many times as we wanted for the day...and they didnt change the lunch..so we ended up eating the same thing for dinner as well. I would recommend the Mandalay buffet which was about the same price, but had a better selection and the food was amazing. If you dont want to buffet there are also restaurants like McDonalds, starbucks, crispy cream, and some others, but for the most part going out to the strip was what we did for the remainder of our trip.Although the strip looks walkable...its not not. Since taxi's weren't the cheapest..we decided to get a 3 day bus pass which was $15(and it was well worth it). The isn't a long wait for buses and it travels right down Las Vegas BLVD, which was perfect, but beware the buses stay at every stop for at least 10 min or more. Even the the buses were cheap....when we went out to the clubs we did end up taking taxi's...and just so everyone knows, there is a line outside every hotel which is extremely only and since we were parties of five we had to wait for the vans.	
Sep 21 2009 	Excalibur - Great Price Great Service	My friend and I spent five nights and six days (Sept 13-18th/09) at The Excalibur. I had read alot of reviews before arriving, some good, some bad. We had a great stay. Our room was on the 24th floor in tower one. Yes, it is an older hotel, but it was clean, our room attendant was awesome and went out of his way to make our stay comfortable. Being also, that when in Vegas, not much time is spent in the room. It was extremely hot during the week and the air conditioner worked perfectly. Our view was ok enough to get some good pictures from the room. Check in was unbelievably fast, and the line up was loooong! Pleasant staff as well. I have nothing negative to say about the hotel other than the elevators could use a bit of better air flow, but a very quick ride I must say, the elevators are also split into sections of the hotel so ours was from the 18th to (I think it was) 27th floors. The service in the casino was great, have to remember how many people are all thirsty all at the same time, if you are THAT thirsty there are other options for beverages and convenient. We went to Thunder from Down Under, now this girls will be up to you, but I would have preferred to spend my money on something else! The men were handsome yes and can dance, and 99% of the time fully clothed. We were lucky to see some &quot;butt cheek&quot; and there was no frontal nudity. There was alot of talk from the host and alot of advertising. Another thing is that the hostess does not check ticket stubs matched with the seats. We had a lady be quite rude and told us to move not realizing there were numbered seats, only to see that lady get the boot from those seats. The highlight was that my friend got pulled up on stage, never saw her smile that big!!! Jello shots helped ease the feeling of wasting my money. We also went to see The Tournament of kings...totally worth it!!! Great show, well done and beautiful costumes. Check out was a breeze as well. Location is good, connecting to New York New York and The MGM. I could write a review about all of Vegas that we saw but the review is for the hotel (and it would be pages long!!!!), my advise is to take a cab everywhere!!!!! They are cheap and plenty and believe me you will regret taking the bus!!!!! The trams and high speed LRT are also good options. DON&quot;T TAKE THE BUS!!! Even the &quot;Deuce&quot;, uh uh! Comfortable shoes are a must and in a pinch you can get some good cheap flip flops at Walgreens....learned that one the hard way! All in all The Excalibur was a great place to stay with good shops and munchie choices. Didn't do the buffet, too much food in a day for me. Was too hot, YES TOO HOT to go to the pool, so no review for that. Easy to fill your days. There were two of us in one room and we only got charged for one person for the $5.00 a day charge. Good times, good times. Fancy no, rasonable yes, and great service. Bed was a little tired but hey, no biggie.	
