Sep 18 2009 	Make your own mind up - For the location and price it can't be beaten	Having read many reviews left by previous guests, I arrived at the Excalibur Hotel for my 13 night stay in August full of dread and fear. I had initially chosen this hotel because of the great location and cost (some of my nightly rates were as low as $22 a night), and had decided that all I needed was a base for my stay, after all I had gone to Vegas to experience the fantastic atmosphere not to take root in a hotel room.Over the past 5 years my husband and I have visited Las Vegas 3 times,staying at the Imperial Palace, Flamingo and Luxor and have found the accomodation to be pleasant and more than adequate for our needs.When we checked in to the Excalibur after 14 hours of travelling, the member of staff was very pleasant, and upgraded with out asking us to a widescreen tower room which had recently been refurbished, and gave us some vouchers for 2 free drinks, 2 free spa passes and 2 free games on the fantasy midway.The room was very clean and tastefully decorated, and was more than adequate for our needs. As we explored the hotel we were very impressed with the cleanliness of the hotel, and the helpfulness of the staff who we encountered. The pool was fantastic, and there was always sunbeds available for guests, even over the labour day weekend which saw a massive increase in the number of guests staying at the hotel. The only drawback was that it was a real suntrap, and the pool had very little shade (unless you hired a cabana for $60 - $100 per day) but the shallow pool and hot tub helped to cool you down.The only negative thing about the hotel was the constant badgering by sales staff to get you to attend a presentation for the new city centre resort - they were placed in all key areas in the hotel, and even though they were not persistant, we found ourselves finding alternative routes through the casino to avoid them.Overall I was really suprised at the quality of the accomodation and would definately stay here again. The rates are cheap, there are plenty of options for food, drink and shopping, and is in a prime location for accessing many of the large hotels. The other advantage of staying at the Excalibur is that it is one of the first stops on the deuce route and so normally has loads of room before hitting the really busy bus stops.	
