Aug 26 2009 	Great Value	Although my husband and I have been to Las Vegas a number of times, this was the first time we stayed at the Excalibur. We were both pleasantly surprised with the value, the service and the quality of the room. Our three night stay cost us just over $100. We were given a complimentary upgrade at check-in. Although we didn't get a view, we did get an upgraded room and a wide screen TV. When we checked into the room, one of the light bulbs was missing on the desk lamp. We called housekeeping and someone was up to replace the bulb within 10 minutes. The exercise room was very nice and included a large selection of cardio equipment, weight machines and a number of wide screen TVs. The use of the exercise room is included in the resort fee, however, if you want to use the showers, sauna, etc. there is an extra $5/day charge. The exercise room looked out onto the pool area. Can't comment on the pool because we never used it but it looked okay from our view point. Check out was a breeze as we used the kiosks where all you have to do is swipe your credit card and you're able to review your bill and print it out on the spot. Excalibur has the all you can eat buffet for $25 but we went to the Mandalay Bay ($35/person) and MGM ($30/person) buffets instead. For the extra $5 we would definitely recommend the Mandalay Bay Buffet. They had fresh blueberries, black berries, great dessert and main meal selection.Not having free wireless was a little disappointing for our teenagers but they were kept busy doing other things. Internet access is available in the room but at a charge of about $14/day. We would definitely stay at the Excalibur again on our next trip to Las Vegas.	
