Aug 25 2009 	Not bad at all...	Just got back today from spending 3 nights at the Excalibur in Las Vegas. Checked in around 3pm on a Saturday. Only spent about 10 minutes in line. Our room was on the 2nd floor of Tower 2. Wished we would have gotten a higher floor or better view but we didn't spend that much time in the room. We booked a widescreen room and it was a decent size. Clean, lights worked, etc. The dresser was a little worn but didn't care... plumbing was okay except the sink took a little long to drain.The casino is a good size and I loved that they had low minimum bet tables. Played roulette and came out even after 3 days which is nice. Dealers were fairly friendly as were the pit bosses. The pool was pretty good, went yesterday morning (Monday) around 11 am and had no problem getting a lounge chair. The music was Top 40 and wasn't too loud.The location is decent- next to NYNY and Luxor- across from MGM Grand. We took the Deuce bus ($7 for 24 hours) after the first night of walking. Didn't sample too much food except the $2.50 hot dog and beer was a steal (for Players Club members only). The only show we saw at Excalibur was the Tournament of Kings, which was entertaining but we wouldn't have paid to see it (not worth the $65ish it costs) if we didn't have a 2 for 1 coupon. We saw Penn &amp; Teller at the Rio which I strong recommend!There were kids around... but I saw them all over Vegas. Still boggles my mind, why would anyone bring a child to Vegas?! But on Sunday afternoon to this morning, only saw a few.Overall, the Excalibur is a good value for the price. I paid an average of $74 a night and I didn't have any major complaints at all. No noise in the room, decent housekeeping, and overall a nice casino. I would go back if I was going on a budget again... but I'd like to keep testing out other hotel/casinos.	
