Aug 5 2009 	Well Worth the value . . .	Overall: Stayed at Excalibur at the end of July for 3 nights for a first time trip to Vegas. We were skeptical at first given some of the reviews and the ratings. We have fairly high standards from previous trips to Mexico, Jamacia and Hawaii. We would say that for the value this was a very nice hotel and casino. There were much fancier and glitzier hotel/casinos like Caesars, Planet Hollywood and Bellagio (to name a few) but for the price this was very nice. Rooms: Upon check-in we had originally booked a standard King size room in Tower I. We asked for an upgrade to Tower II in a widescreen room and were given it for free. (Never hurts to ask). The room was very nice on the 25th floor and had a nice view of the pools. The bed was very comfortable and the room was quiet. It was nothing fancy or over the top, but you spend very little time in the room anyways. Casino: The casino was great because even on the weekend and later at night, you could find $5 tables without a problem. Also the dealers were very friendly at the Craps table as they taught me how to play and it paid off. The casino never seemed very busy. The drinks were expensive unless you were gambling, then they were free. We did not have any problems with Timeshare pressure as when we told them no, they left us alone.Food: We did not eat at any restraunts here, but it was nice having a Starbucks for my wife and Monster enery drinks for me. On one side note, we ate at Casa Di Amore and it was fantastic!! We also had the seafood buffet at the Rio and it was great as well. Pools: The pools were somewhat busy, but because there were so many, you could find chairs without a problem. Overall, we would definitely stay here for the money as the location is fantastic and the hotel/casino is of great value! You definitely come to Vegas for the overall experience, not to spend all your time at one hotel! Hope this helps!!	
