Jul 31 2009 	Great Value Great Location Will stay again!	Timeshare People: Yes they are guarding the entrances, and even though I had read about them no one told me what to look out for or how to bypass them. They are the friendly people in the blue blazers that act like the care about you when you walk in. If someone says the following to you: &quot;Where are you guys from&quot;, or &quot;Is this your first time here&quot; when you walk in the door they are most likely timeshare people. Simply look at them and say no thank you. They know the drill and leave you alone; the key is to not stop walking. The check in desk is to the left of the main entrance when you go in the hotel, you can sight see later. Check In: There was a long line to check in, but it moved quickly. We waited maybe 10 minutes, not bad at all. The young lady that checked us in was very nice and the whole process at the desk took about 3 minutes.Room: After reading several reviews I opted for the safer bet in my opinion and booked a wide screen room. These rooms are in Tower 2. We were not disappointed. The room was clean, the beds were comfortable, and the air conditioning worked great. The showers drained a little slow, but I have that happen at most hotels. TV was nice, but we never used it really, it’s Vegas.Cleaning Staff: Our cleaning staff was awesome. Some days we didn’t leave the room until after 1pm, but our room was always cleaned when we returned. At any hotel I like to leave a $5 tip on the nightstand each day before we go out. I leave a note requesting extra towels every day, cups, etc., and this has always gotten my requests filled no problems, the Excalibur was no exception. At the least I figure the tip gives them extra motivation to clean my room regardless of the time I leave.Location: This hotel is in the best location in my opinion. It is a cheap $15 + tip taxi fare from the airport or an easy drive if you rent a car. If you choose other hotels like Bally’s you have to fight the strip traffic, which is horrible at best. It’s a 20-25 min walk from here to the Bellagio which is in the middle of the strip. Families: If you are one of the many people that say hey, I want to take my kid to “Sin City” this info is for you. This hotel has a several things that would appeal to kids, mainly an overpriced arcade, and a statue of Sponge Bob. *Remember this is Vegas, so Sponge Bob is roughly 15ft from a Liquor Bar, 25ft from the Gaming Tables, and depending on the time of day only 40ft from women in very little clothing dancing on a stage. Not to mention if you decided to go for a stroll down the strip the porn pushers will introduce your kid to enough porn to last them until they are in college. They will like the pool though!General: This hotel is a great value, clean, friendly, and has a great vibe. If you want luxury the MGM is across the street and is very nice, but I stayed 4 nights at Excalibur for the price of 1 and a half there. I wanted to spend my money on other things. Remember though, I booked a wide screen room in tower 2, I can’t speak for the cheaper rooms.	
