Jul 27 2009 	Good introduction for 1st timers to Vegas	We had a room in the older Tower 1 but it had terrific views of the surrounding mountains, airport and southern end of The Strip. (A full moon one night was an amazing sight!) The room itself was spacious, quiet and very cool thanks to great airconditioning but a little tired in decor and furniture and the king bed mattress was uncomfortable with what I presumed to be a broken spring. Housekeeping was good except for the 1 towel with a great big hole in the middle of it! The all-you-can-eat 24 hour $25 buffet was terrific! Great value and great choices every time, we loved this! The Camelot Steakhouse was pricey but delivered ... a delicious meal (the most amazing salad dish accompanying the best steak). The Casino itself was very heavy with cigarette smoke, moreso than other Casinos on The Strip and EVERY time you entered or left the hotel, you were harrassed by &quot;show ticket sellers&quot; at the entrances which got rather annoying time after time! Overall, for the price this hotel provides a good introduction to Las Vegas and The Strip. Dining, souvenirs and amenities are cheap and cheerful, however next time I'd go for a hotel more towards the middle of The Strip and one a bit classier.	
