Jul 26 2009	A good value	Went on a trip with some friends and stayed 4 nights at the Excalibur. We were in the newer section of the hotel and while pleasantly surprised with the room, our view was of the roof. Guess we can't have everything.The hotel is on the corner of the strip and Tropicana, with MGM Grand, New York New York and the apparently soon to be demolished/renovated (?) Tropicana Hotel. The price is the biggest draw as well cheaper gaming tables. My room mate and friends enjoyed the penny and 2-cent slots and made a fun time of the trip, for sure. I did well playing $5 craps and $10 black-jack. The all-day Buffet is not a bad deal, but wish they changed the food from lunch to dinner. Maybe it was just the day we were there, so we got tired of the food and ate somewhere else the other days. (Tried the MGM dinner Buffet. The food was much better, but also pricier.)The comps are generous for the amount of playing I did. Do get yourself a MGM Player's Card which allows you to accummulate points at several properties. We got some pretty good comps for meals (at least one meal each day) as well late check-out. I think I came out a bit ahead at the end of the stay, even counting the $$ saved from the freebie meals. I'm a newbie on the comps thing, so had I known we should have charged all the meals to the room, I might have gotten everything for free. I learned from that!For those of you complaining about pay-to-use internet access in the room. suggest instead that you go to the food court where Krispy Kreme is --- they have free wi-fi there, if you absolutely must check your email, etc. While I was doing just that, there were 3 other people doing the same thing. :)I've recommended the hotel to some friends and they also had a great stay, so I guess it's not really too bad, for the money.	
