Apr 30 2009 	Great value for the money!!!	My husband and I stayed at the Excalibur for four nights from April 24 - 28, 2009. We checked in around 12:00 pm, and found the process efficient and the desk clerk friendly. We have stayed at the Excalibur twice previously, and found that both our room and the service we received met our expectations and were consistent with our previous experiences. The Excalibur is a very nice hotel for those travelers who are not interested in spending large sums of money on hotel rooms. The rooms are large, clean, and come with all the basic amenities (toiletries, a hair dryer, ironing board, etc.) but are not fancy or lavish. My main complaint with the Excalibur is the excessive presence of timeshare sellers located throughout the hotel. You are approached every time you enter or leave the tower where your room is located, when you go to the fast food restaurants or buffet on the second level, or when you approach the lobby area. My husband and I just smile and say &quot;No, thanks&quot; as we walk by, as we know they are just doing their job. However, it quickly becomes tiring.Other things to note: The renovated pool area was very nice, and there were adequate lounge chairs considering the occupancy level of the hotel. The poolside restaurant offered very generous portions at very fair prices - my husband got a footlong hotdog for $5.The buffet offers standard fare, and there is a $25 special being offered right now for an all-day pass to the buffet. The Italian restaurant and Steakhouse are also offering prix fixe menus.There is adequate parking in a garage behind the hotel, which is located closest to Tower 2 (the tower by the pool). Tower 1 is located closest to the Strip, if this makes a difference to you.Overall, we had a great time at the Excalibur, and would have no problem recommending it to family and friends.	
