oking. This includes the gym that has to be paid even for hotel guests which is surprising. The spa has everything you’d need for an hour or so of pampering but does have separate facilities for men and women that is the only problem. My wife and myself were the only people in our respective spas when we went and it was a shame we couldn’t have been unisex.The pool area is excellent at the Excalibur. It’s huge and even though a couple of the pools were shut when we were there, as the hotel was quiet, there was more than enough room around the pool. The pool bar was excellent aswell.The outlets village at the south end of the strip is very easy to get to by the deuce bus and is around 2 miles away. Is only a couple of dollars each and is great for some bargains.The Excalibur is a great value hotel to stay and was impressed with the room we had. If a cheaper hotel at the south end of the strip is what you’re looking for then its difficult to fault it. I would definitely stay here again.	
