Apr 20 2009 	21st Birthday - Nothing special Nothing terrible either.	As you go through all of these reviews you are going to see hundreds of cases where people receive bad customer service. I have stayed at the Excalibur multiple times now and have been satisfied with what I pay for. First of all, you need to know what is going on in Vegas during your trip. Huge conventions cause a lot of chaos among customer service counters at many hotels because of the massive amount of group bookings and people wanting the five star treatment anywhere they go.If you at this hotel and are arriving on Thursday-Saturday after 12pm the waits for your room are going to be extensive at every hotel. When you book your room and choose one king or two queens, remember you are booking upon availability. With the economy the way it is, these cheaper hotels are getting more business than the expensive ones.If you are expecting a perfectly cleaned, spotless room at any of the hotels that have been in Vegas for 15+ years you are not going to get them very often. Excalibur has done a bit of remodeling with some WIDESCREEN ROOMS. They are nice and very adequate for anyone going there to have fun and party. They are pretty basic though, you are not going to get your coffee or anything special in the room. THAT IS WHY THEY ARE $40-$80 MIDWEEK AND $80 -$150 WEEKEND. They look a little more classy in the pictures than they actually are. Everything is just a little newer. If you want a decent room for a cheap price this is the way to go.Service at the Excalibur is okay.If you are respectful of the staff they will treat you the same. Housekeeping has always done a decent job of picking up the room while we were away. They will be a lot more thorough if you leave them $5 a day. You will find the occasional hooker/prostitute at the bars if you are staying here with kids. They don't make it very obvious so don't expect to see a girl with her skirt hiked up so you can see half her butt everywhere you go down there.There are a lot of younger couples and college kids that stay at this hotel also because of the cost. Don't expect a quiet nights sleep everynight. You will not get it. The food is at the bottom end of what you kind find on the strip but it is cheap. McDonald's in house very cheap $1 Menu for breakfast/lunch. There are also some other options by the food court. Good food is close thought at Mandalay Bay or MGM. They both are within 15 minutes walking distance.The location is near the South end of the strip. You are only on a street corner between Luxor and NYNY. It is a very long walk to get to the North side near the Wynn and Riviera. The casino is relatively smoky and you definitely can smell it. Don't be surprised when you get there. This casino has been in Vegas since 1990, back then it was primarily a gambling town. It is older and is not going to be remodeled on the casino level anytime soon. People that complain about this casino needing a face lift are right but it's not going to happen so don't complain about when you get back. If you are going to be out and about shopping down the strip. I recommend staying at one of the Harrah's properties: Flamingo, Paris, Bally's or Harrah's. They are all in the same price range with Paris being the most upscale.Gambling at Excalibur has always been lucky for me. The slots have a decent payout percentage and is definitely better than the highscale properties. This casino has paid for itself many times over so they are in the black no matter what. MGM owns and runs so join there Players Club because you can gamble at all of the casinos right around it to earn comps as well. The table games at excalibur range from $5 UPWARD. Beware the farther down the strip you go and the later in the day you play the minimum does go up. Many big casinos range in the $15 - $100 minimum bet limits after 4:00PM.Good luck if you choose Excalibur and it will be adequate if you know what to expect.	
Apr 17 2009 	It was great. Great value for money and very clean rooms on the strip	We stayed for a week (6th April to 13th April) and found the hotel to be great. We were very concerned about the quality of the hotel prior to travelling as most reviews seemed to be so negative but this wasn’t the case. The room was very, very clean. The toiletries were replaced each day along with fresh towels. The day before arriving I e mailed and asked for a complimentary upgrade to a room that had been refurbished and with a view of the strip and this is exactly what we got! At no extra cost or tipping. We overlooked New York New York hotel , the Statue of Liberty and MGM. The hotel is in a fantastic location. You just walk across the bridge and come to the strip (2 minutes) from there you can walk to all the sights. We walked everywhere except for Downtown Vegas when we caught the Deuce bus (7 dollar for a 24 hour pass each). The casino is smoky but they all are. However if you want a reasonable casino where you can play the machines at a realistic cost than this is the hotel to visit. It appears, having spoken to a number of other visitors that gamblers travel up and down the strip to play the tables and machine at the Excalibur. I know that many people criticise Las Vegas. This was my first visit and I loved it but if you’re looking for a busy holiday with plenty to do in a reasonably cheap hotel that costs a lot less that then many other hotels on the strip then you can’t beat the Excalibur.P.S. The swimming pools were great also. We never had a problem finding a sun bed (9am or 2pm) even though it was the Easter week-end and the weather was good too. P.P.S I usually stay in 5 star hotels so to write this positive review is a surprise to us too!	
Apr 16 2009 	Great Hotel	We stayed at the Excalibur for 5 nights in April and had a great time. We chose the hotel due to its location and price, being one of the least expensive venues on the Strip. If you're on a budget, don't waste your money on expensive pretentious hotels when you can save your cash for gambling, shopping and drinking! You can stay here and walk 2 minutes from your room to be in NYNY, Luxor or MGM. Remember; Location, Location, Location!Given that most of your time in Vegas is probably spent in the casino/bars/pool/shops (delete as appropriate), the room was more than adequate; very clean, big comfy bed, double shower and TV. And this was just a standard room!The casino itself was a little smokey as others have mentioned but only noticeable if you spend hours on the tables. The pool was lovely and a bonus to have an adult pool without the screaming kids and with a bit of music playing to create a lively atmosphere. There is a Pleasure Pit in the casino with a some good looking dancers strutting their stuff, although nowhere near the calibre of the PussyCat Doll Lounge at Caesars or the Croupiers at Planet Hollywood! Sorry Girls!Avoid the buffet too. There are far too many other choices nearby to waste time with queues and mediocre food. Plenty of snack options upstairs and also a Krispy Kreme which has free WiFi. There's also a 'Dog and Draft' offer at the bar for a hotdog and small beer for $2.50. Bargain!My advice is stay at Excalibur, chill by the pool all day, take a few steps over to Coyote Ugly (NYNY) and the West Wing Bar at MGM for Happy hour (5-8?) before heading out on the town where the real fun begins. If you're sober enough when you get back then a few hands of BlackJack or a Bud at Dicks is a perfect finish to a Vegas day.	
Apr 16 2009 	Great Place for the price!	My husband and I stayed at the Excalibur 4/7/09-4/11/09. Loved the location. At first it was a little confusing on how to get down to the strip. But after just about a 1/2 an hour we got our bearings and it was VERY easy to get to NYNY, MGM, and down to the strip. We should have asked someone but had a lot of fun exploring. Finding the tram to get to Luxor and Mandalay Bay was every easy. However we mostly took the moving sidewalks that are all indoors. It is not a bad walk to Planet Hollywood also.We had the standard room.The room was just fine. Very clean! The carpet was ok. We had a smoking room so it had a few very small burns but it was clean. We stayed on the 2nd floor and had a view of the Luxor. It was awesome that the window opened. Only about 3 inches but the weather was cool this time of year and it helped get the smoke out of the room. The beds were very comfortable. We did have a safe in the room. While it is not a 5 star hotel it was WELL worth the price.I did see a few children. However it was not out of control. The casino was great. Lot's of penny slots and penny poker. The craps table's were HOT. We got the all day buffet only once and that was enough. Breakfast was very good but lunch and dinner was well... awful. We ordered room service one eveing and the food was good and the service was fast. The only thing we did not like is that they did not tell us that we had to set it up so we could charge to the room when we checked in, So we had to pay cash for the food. Which was fine but we would have much rather have charged it to the room.The best advice I can give you is DO NOT do one of the timeshare deal's. They offered us a show and $100 in casino credit if we did it. We were told that it would only take 1 1/2 hours... Took 2 1/2 hours the show was worthless (V at planet hollywood)and only gave us $50. What a waste of time.	
Apr 15 2009 	Good hotel but you can find better...	We stayed at the Excalibur as the room rates seem to be very good and they provided child friendly activities for our young son.We arrived at the Excalibur mid-afternoon and found a long line to check in. It wasn't bad though as they had most of their check in desk open and they were relatively fast in checking everyone in. Our room was in Tower 1 and faced Tower 2, with no real views. It was fine as we didn't spend much time in our room looking out the window. Our room was a bit on the small side and is definately showing some serious wear and tear. The chairs were scratched up and needed some new upholstery. The beds were horrible! You could feel every spring on your back as you rolled around. The pillows weren't any better! Your head just sank through the pillows. You needed at least 2-3 for you to feel them, LOL. We also found that the A/C unit in our room was not working! But instead of the front desk moving us (they said to just wait out the repair - I was too tired to argue), they had maintenance come in and actually replace the huge unit. We couldn't even get comfortable as we had people in and out of our rooms during the repair. After the repair, the area was filthy and I had to get one of the cleaning ladies to come in and vacuum and she wasn't the most friendly person to deal with.I will say though, that the hotel is in an awesome location and was nearby all the attractions that we were interested in seeing. But I probably won't stay at the Excalibur again though. Most people come to Vegas to party and have fun, then you use your room to rest and sleep. But with the bed and pillows like we had, forget it! Pay a few bucks more and either upgrade your room (I assume that more expensive rooms have better beds) or go to another hotel.... Oh... The Excalibur does have a Midway for kids to play games and win prizes. A lot of the video games were in major disrepair though, but the Midway games were fun.Now, would I recommend the Excalibur? I would say no, but it does have its perks and I guess you'd have to weight them out yourselves.	
Apr 15 2009 	Dismal and depressing	A small group selected this hotel for our stay while bowling nationals--I assume for its lower price compared to the nicer resorts. I hate casinos. They are noisy and big. This one smelled of smoke (They still allow smoking inside? Join the 21st century, folks!) was dim, and dingy. The room was large enough, but the temperature control fan and the bathroom fan were noisy. (Will wake your room partner if you need to turn on the light in the bathroom during the night!) Small sofa (hideabed?) smelled like pee. No bathtub, shower only. No robes. Only Pepsi products, no Coca Cola. Sheets came untucked easily. Charged extra for Internet, not working the second day...only good thing to say: Elevators were quick.	
Apr 15 2009 	Rooms Hotel Service Cleanliness .. TERRIBLE!	We booked our rooms thru American Airlines Vacations. Read the reviews on-line for the hotel, thought they were OK .. Don't believe it. Took forever to check-in, they also don't tell you about the &quot;resort fee&quot; which is an additional charge. We finally got to our room and was surprised by someone in our bathroom who was cleaning an overflowing toilet. I called the front desk and after much discussion was moved to another room which was equally bad (without the toilet problem though) .. I again called the front desk and asked for a different room - one in Tower II (which I found out was newly renovated) .. after must discussion, whe agreed to send me to a Tower II room for an additional fee of $20.00/nite which I refused and she immediately dropped the fee to $10.00/nite .. I asked what kind of SCAM were they running .. and hung up.Needless to say, we didn't stay at the Excalibur and would not recommend it to anyone I know. We travel to Vegas 5-6 times every year and have never had this kind of problem. For the record, we stayed at the Pallazzo instead .. and, I would highly recommend that hotel!	
