Apr 14 2009 	Great Hotel let down slightly by poor housekeeping!	We stopped here for 7 nights from the 1st April 2009 and a had a great time at the hotel. We were given room 26212 (26th floor in Tower 2) and found the room to be excellent with great views from the window (see pics I uploaded). The bathroom was huge (although no bath, only a shower cubicle) and the room was well equiped &amp; in good order.My only criticism of Excalibur is the slightly shabby housekeeping throughout the hotel. We found our room cleaned but the bathroom wasnt wiped down very well each day with soap marks left on the worktops &amp; the soap not changed daily. Also we noticed that room service trolleys were being left out in the hallways outside peoples rooms for hours 7 hours at a time and the elevators were not hoovered very often leaving the carpets covered in bits.One other small thing that may be worth mentioning is the stealth fee of $1 per night for telephone usage, regardless of whether you plan to use the phone or not?! I was a bit annoyed at having to pay this, whats wrong with only charging people for the calls they make??These are only small criticisms but did stop me from giving the hotel a 5 out of 5 rating. But they would not stop us from staying here again, as the hotel is very nice and great value for money.	
